thread.title: Market set to open lower

title: Market set to open lower
text:
Thu, Jul 23, 2015, 7:08 AM AEST - Australia Markets open in 2 hrs 52 mins Market set to open lower AAP â€“ 20 minutes ago Print 
The Australian market looks set to fall after a weak session on Wall Street due to disappointment with earnings reports from the likes of Apple and Microsoft. 
At 0645 AEST on Thursday, the September share price index futures contract was down two points at 5,550. 
There is no major economic news scheduled for release on Thursday. 
In company news, Fortescue Metals, Newcrest Mining and BC Iron are due to release quarterly production reports, and construction firm CIMIC will post its half year financial results. 
Macquarie Group holds its annual general meeting in Sydney. 
The market fell on Wednesday, ending a six day winning streak. 
the benchmark S&P/ASX200 index shed 92.1 points, or 1.61 per cent, to 5,614.6 points and the broader All Ordinaries index dropped 85 points, or 1.49 per cent, to 5,603.5. @y7finance on Twitter, become a fan on Facebook Terms
